WEBVTT

00:00:02.999 --> 00:00:05.542
CHARLES DARWIN ONCE TOOK 
A RIDE ON ONE OF THESE

00:00:05.542 --> 00:00:07.250
AND IT WAS SOMETHING 
ABOUT THEIR SHELLS

00:00:07.250 --> 00:00:08.999
THAT GAVE HIM THE FIRST HINT

00:00:08.999 --> 00:00:10.999
THAT LIVING CREATURES 
CHANGE OVER TIME.

00:00:10.999 --> 00:00:13.667
( crunching )

00:00:13.667 --> 00:00:15.999
THE GIANT TORTOISES 
OF THE GALAPAGOS ISLANDS

00:00:15.999 --> 00:00:17.999
ARE AMONG THE MANY 
UNIQUE ANIMALS HERE...

00:00:17.999 --> 00:00:18.999
OKAY, I'M SORRY, 
I'M SORRY.

00:00:18.999 --> 00:00:20.999
Alda: 
THAT GOT DARWIN TO THINKING

00:00:20.999 --> 00:00:23.667
ABOUT HOW NEW SPECIES COME 
INTO BEING.

00:00:25.999 --> 00:00:29.999
TODAY THE ISLANDS' CREATURES 
STILL AMAZE THEIR VISITORS

00:00:29.999 --> 00:00:32.999
AND PROVIDE INSIGHTS 
INTO HOW EVOLUTION WORKS.

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:34.999
I HAVE GOOD 
BEGINNER'S LUCK.

00:00:34.999 --> 00:00:35.999
I'M ALAN ALDA.

00:00:35.999 --> 00:00:38.999
JOIN ME AND THE CREATURES 
THAT INSPIRED DARWIN

00:00:38.999 --> 00:00:40.999
AS WE VOYAGE TO THE GALAPAGOS.

