00:01:21.999 --> 00:01:24.999
IN 1831, AT THE AGE OF 22

00:01:24.999 --> 00:01:26.999
CHARLES DARWIN SET OFF 
ON A VOYAGE

00:01:26.999 --> 00:01:30.999
THAT WOULD CHANGE NOT ONLY 
HIS LIFE BUT OURS AS WELL.

00:01:30.999 --> 00:01:33.959
THE NATURALIST ON A 
BRITISH NAVAL SHIP, THE BEAGLE

00:01:33.959 --> 00:01:36.999
DARWIN TRAVELED AROUND 
SOUTH AMERICA AND BEYOND.

00:01:36.999 --> 00:01:38.999
WHAT HE SAW ON AN 
ISOLATED GROUP OF ISLANDS

00:01:38.999 --> 00:01:40.999
OUT HERE IN THE PACIFIC

00:01:40.999 --> 00:01:44.542
BEGAN AN INTELLECTUAL VOYAGE 
THAT WOULD LAST SOME 20 YEARS

00:01:44.542 --> 00:01:47.999
AND WOULD CULMINATE IN THE THEN 
SHOCKING IDEA THAT LIVING THINGS

00:01:47.999 --> 00:01:50.999
ARE NOT DESIGNED ACCORDING 
TO AN UNCHANGEABLE PLAN

00:01:50.999 --> 00:01:53.667
BUT INSTEAD ARE SHAPED 
BY THE WORLD AROUND THEM.

00:01:57.999 --> 00:02:00.999
WHEN THE BEAGLE FINALLY 
ANCHORED HERE IN THE GALAPAGOS

00:02:00.999 --> 00:02:02.999
IN SEPTEMBER OF 1835

00:02:02.999 --> 00:02:05.417
DARWIN WAS VERY EXCITED 
ABOUT COMING HERE.

00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:07.999
HE WAS REALLY FASCINATED 
WITH THE GEOLOGY OF THE PLACE

00:02:07.999 --> 00:02:11.542
PARTICULARLY THE VOLCANIC 
ORIGINS OF THESE ISLANDS.

00:02:11.542 --> 00:02:13.834
BUT WHEN HE ACTUALLY SET FOOT 
ON THE SHORE

00:02:13.834 --> 00:02:15.999
HE WAS VERY DISAPPOINTED 
IN THIS PLACE.

00:02:15.999 --> 00:02:17.125
IN FACT, THIS IS WHAT HE WROTE:

00:02:17.125 --> 00:02:20.999
"NOTHING COULD BE LESS INVITING 
THAN THE FIRST APPEARANCE.

00:02:20.999 --> 00:02:23.999
"A BROKEN FIELD 
OF BLACK, BASALTIC LAVA

00:02:23.999 --> 00:02:26.999
"IS EVERYWHERE COVERED 
BY A STUNTED BRUSHWOOD

00:02:26.999 --> 00:02:29.000
"WHICH SHOWS LITTLE 
SIGNS OF LIFE.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:31.999
"THE DRY AND PARCHED SURFACE

00:02:31.999 --> 00:02:33.667
"HAVING BEEN HEATED 
BY THE NOONDAY SUN

00:02:33.667 --> 00:02:36.999
"GAVE THE AIR A CLOSE 
AND SULTRY FEELING

00:02:36.999 --> 00:02:38.834
LIKE THAT FROM A STOVE."

00:02:40.999 --> 00:02:43.999
600 MILES OFF 
THE SOUTH AMERICAN COAST

00:02:43.999 --> 00:02:46.999
THE GALAPAGOS ISLANDS ARE 
ACTUALLY THE TIPS OF VOLCANOES

00:02:46.999 --> 00:02:49.999
THAT HAVE PUSHED THEIR WAY 
ABOVE THE OCEAN SURFACE.

00:02:49.999 --> 00:02:51.999
THE OLDEST ISLANDS WERE FORMED

00:02:51.999 --> 00:02:53.999
SOME TWO TO 
THREE MILLION YEARS AGO.

00:02:53.999 --> 00:02:56.999
THE YOUNGEST, 
INCLUDING THE BIGGEST, ISABELA

00:02:56.999 --> 00:02:59.999
ARE A FEW HUNDRED 
THOUSAND YEARS OLD

00:02:59.999 --> 00:03:01.999
WITH VOLCANOES THAT STILL ERUPT.

00:03:05.999 --> 00:03:07.542
MY VISIT TO THE GALAPAGOS 
IS TO TAKE ME

00:03:07.542 --> 00:03:10.999
TO OVER HALF THE DOZEN 
OR SO MAJOR ISLANDS

00:03:10.999 --> 00:03:15.250
INCLUDING ONE WHOSE VOLCANIC 
ORIGINS ARE ONLY TOO APPARENT.

00:03:15.250 --> 00:03:16.834
Alda: 
THESE ROCKS LOOK

00:03:16.834 --> 00:03:18.000
LIKE THEY'RE LAID OUT 
IN A CIRCLE.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:20.959
Woman: 
YEAH, THIS IS 
DEVIL'S CROWN.

00:03:20.959 --> 00:03:21.999
IT'S AN OLD 
ERODED CRATER

00:03:21.999 --> 00:03:23.999
THAT'S VERY SHALLOW HERE 
IN THE MIDDLE.

00:03:23.999 --> 00:03:25.999
WE'RE IN THE 
MIDDLE OF A CRATER--

00:03:25.999 --> 00:03:26.999
A VOLCANIC CRATER?

00:03:26.999 --> 00:03:28.417
YEAH, IT'S NOT GOING 
TO ERUPT, THOUGH

00:03:28.417 --> 00:03:29.834
DON'T WORRY.

00:03:29.834 --> 00:03:30.999
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

00:03:30.999 --> 00:03:31.999
IT'S OLD-- 
IT'S ALL ERODED.

00:03:31.999 --> 00:03:33.999
I'VE SEEN A LOT OF 
OLD THINGS ERUPT--

00:03:33.999 --> 00:03:35.000
ME!

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.999
I'M REALLY 
SURPRISED AT HOW 
LUSH EVERYTHING IS.

00:03:37.999 --> 00:03:39.250
THAT'S THE EL NIÑO?

00:03:39.250 --> 00:03:41.999
Alda: 
MY GUIDE ON THE TRIP 
IS LYNN FOWLER

00:03:41.999 --> 00:03:45.834
A BIOLOGIST WHO HAS SPENT 
MUCH OF HER LIFE IN THE ISLANDS.

00:03:45.834 --> 00:03:46.999
WHAT IS THIS 
TRAIL HERE?

00:03:46.999 --> 00:03:49.000
THAT'S A 
LAND IGUANA TRAIL.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
SO AT THE END OF 
THIS TRAIL WE MIGHT 
FIND AN IGUANA?

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.999
WE MIGHT FIND ONE-- 
LET'S SEE.

00:03:52.999 --> 00:03:56.959
Alda: 
AND HERE, AS IF WAITING 
PATIENTLY FOR OUR ARRIVAL

00:03:56.959 --> 00:03:59.999
IS A CREATURE THAT DARWIN WAS 
NOT IMMEDIATELY IMPRESSED BY.

00:03:59.999 --> 00:04:02.417
WHEN DARWIN FIRST SAW 
THESE LAND IGUANAS

00:04:02.417 --> 00:04:04.999
HE THOUGHT THEY LOOKED 
SLOW AND STUPID.

00:04:04.999 --> 00:04:07.999
IN FACT, THERE'S A FUNNY STORY 
HE TELLS ABOUT THAT.

00:04:10.999 --> 00:04:14.999
DARWIN WAS WATCHING 
A LAND IGUANA BURROW

00:04:14.999 --> 00:04:16.999
MAKING A HOLE 
SOMEWHAT LIKE THIS ONE

00:04:16.999 --> 00:04:18.542
WITH JUST HIS TAIL STICKING OUT.

00:04:18.542 --> 00:04:20.999
AND DARWIN GAVE 
THE TAIL A LITTLE YANK

00:04:20.999 --> 00:04:23.999
AND THE IGUANA BACKED OUT 
OF THE HOLE AND TURNED AROUND

00:04:23.999 --> 00:04:26.999
AND LOOKED AT HIM, AS IF TO SAY, 
"WHAT DID YOU DO THAT FOR?"

00:04:29.999 --> 00:04:31.999
WHAT DARWIN INTERPRETED 
AS STUPIDITY

00:04:31.999 --> 00:04:33.000
IN THE ISLANDS' LAND IGUANAS

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:36.417
IS IN FACT AN EXTRAORDINARY 
INDIFFERENCE TO HUMANS

00:04:36.417 --> 00:04:39.125
THAT'S SHARED BY ALL 
THE GALAPAGOS ANIMAL LIFE

00:04:39.125 --> 00:04:42.999
AND THAT DARWIN REPEATEDLY NOTED 
IN HIS ACCOUNT OF HIS VOYAGE.

00:04:47.999 --> 00:04:50.999
HE TOOK ADVANTAGE OF IT 
IN HIS SEVERAL ENCOUNTERS

00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:52.999
WITH THE GALAPAGOS ISLANDS' 
MOST FAMOUS RESIDENTS

00:04:52.999 --> 00:04:55.250
THE GIANT TORTOISES:

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:57.999
"AS I WAS WALKING ALONG, 
I MET TWO LARGE TORTOISES

00:04:57.999 --> 00:05:01.667
"EACH OF WHICH MUST HAVE WEIGHED 
AT LEAST 200 POUNDS.

00:05:01.667 --> 00:05:03.999
"THESE HUGE REPTILES 
SEEMED TO MY FANCY

00:05:03.999 --> 00:05:06.999
"LIKE SOME ANTEDILUVIAN ANIMALS.

00:05:06.999 --> 00:05:08.999
"I WAS ALWAYS AMUSED 
WHEN OVERTAKING

00:05:08.999 --> 00:05:11.417
"ONE OF THESE GREAT MONSTERS 
AS IT WAS QUIETLY PACING ALONG

00:05:11.417 --> 00:05:13.999
"TO SEE HOW SUDDENLY, 
THE INSTANT I PASSED

00:05:13.999 --> 00:05:17.667
"IT WOULD DRAW IN ITS HEAD AND 
LEGS, AND UTTERING A DEEP HISS

00:05:17.667 --> 00:05:21.125
FALL TO THE GROUND WITH A 
HEAVY SOUND, AS IF STRUCK DEAD."

00:05:21.125 --> 00:05:23.417
( tortoise hisses loudly )

00:05:25.999 --> 00:05:28.667
"I FREQUENTLY GOT 
ON THEIR BACKS

00:05:28.667 --> 00:05:31.999
"AND THEN GIVING A FEW RAPS ON 
THE HINDER PART OF THEIR SHELLS

00:05:31.999 --> 00:05:34.667
"THEY WOULD RISE UP 
AND WALK AWAY

00:05:34.667 --> 00:05:36.999
BUT I FOUND IT VERY DIFFICULT 
TO KEEP MY BALANCE."

00:05:36.999 --> 00:05:41.000
( crunching )

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:42.999
( giggling )

00:05:42.999 --> 00:05:45.999
TODAY VISITORS TO THE GALAPAGOS 
USUALLY PAY THEIR RESPECTS

00:05:45.999 --> 00:05:47.999
TO THE HANDFUL OF GIANT 
TORTOISES THAT ARE HOUSED

00:05:47.999 --> 00:05:50.999
AT THE RESEARCH STATION HERE 
NAMED FOR CHARLES DARWIN

00:05:50.999 --> 00:05:52.999
ALTHOUGH GETTING TO FEED THEM

00:05:52.999 --> 00:05:55.000
IS A PRIVILEGE RESERVED 
FOR THE FOOLHARDY.

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:57.834
HELLO.

00:05:57.834 --> 00:05:58.999
( chomp )

00:05:58.999 --> 00:06:00.999
WHAT A LOOK 
IN HIS EYE.

00:06:00.999 --> 00:06:03.999
( in amazement ): 
OY-OY-OY!

00:06:06.999 --> 00:06:08.999
MY PROBLEM IS 
I NOT ONLY SAW E.T.

00:06:08.999 --> 00:06:10.667
I ALSO SAW JURASSIC PARK.

00:06:10.667 --> 00:06:13.250
Alda: 
IN DARWIN'S DAY, 
THE GIANT TORTOISES

00:06:13.250 --> 00:06:15.542
WERE STILL BEING HAULED AWAY 
BY THE THOUSANDS

00:06:15.542 --> 00:06:17.417
TO PROVIDE FRESH MEAT 
FOR WHALING SHIPS.

00:06:17.417 --> 00:06:19.125
THAT'S A LITTLE 
TOO CLOSE TO 
MY FINGERS--

00:06:19.125 --> 00:06:20.999
YOU CAN HAVE IT.

00:06:20.999 --> 00:06:23.417
Alda: 
THE GOVERNOR 
OF THE GALAPAGOS TOLD DARWIN

00:06:23.417 --> 00:06:25.999
THAT HE COULD TELL 
BY THE SHAPE OF ITS SHELL

00:06:25.999 --> 00:06:27.999
WHICH ISLAND 
A TORTOISE CAME FROM.

00:06:27.999 --> 00:06:30.999
THIS SADDLE-BACKED TORTOISE, 
FOR INSTANCE

00:06:30.999 --> 00:06:33.999
COMES FROM 
THE ISLAND OF ESPAÑOLA.

00:06:33.999 --> 00:06:35.999
AT THE TIME, 
DARWIN PAID LITTLE ATTENTION

00:06:35.999 --> 00:06:37.999
TO THE GOVERNOR'S CLAIM

00:06:37.999 --> 00:06:41.667
BUT IT WAS TO BE THE FOUNDATION 
FOR EVERYTHING THAT FOLLOWED.

00:06:47.999 --> 00:06:49.999
SOON HE SAW FOR HIMSELF 
HOW CREATURES

00:06:49.999 --> 00:06:53.999
COULD BE RECOGNIZABLY DIFFERENT 
FROM ONE ISLAND TO THE NEXT.

00:06:59.999 --> 00:07:02.959
THESE MOCKINGBIRDS, 
LIKE THE SADDLE-BACKED TORTOISE

00:07:02.959 --> 00:07:04.250
ARE FROM THE ISLAND OF ESPAÑOLA.

00:07:04.250 --> 00:07:05.999
( chirping loudly )

00:07:06.999 --> 00:07:09.999
Man: 
THESE MOCKINGBIRDS 
ARE HAVING A FLICK FIGHT.

00:07:09.999 --> 00:07:12.125
THEY FLICK THEIR WINGS 
AND THEIR TAIL BACK AND FORTH

00:07:12.125 --> 00:07:13.999
AS A TERRITORIAL DISPLAY

00:07:13.999 --> 00:07:16.999
BETWEEN TWO BIG GROUPS OF 
MOCKINGBIRDS THAT ARE FAMILIES

00:07:16.999 --> 00:07:18.999
AND THEY'RE DISPUTING 
WHAT'S GOING ON

00:07:18.999 --> 00:07:20.667
AT THE TERRITORIAL BOUNDARY.

00:07:20.667 --> 00:07:23.999
SO THEY DO THIS 
BIG DISPLAY SAYING, YOU KNOW

00:07:23.999 --> 00:07:24.999
"IF YOU CROSS THIS BOUNDARY

00:07:24.999 --> 00:07:27.000
"THIS IS WHAT'S GOING 
TO HAPPEN TO YOU.

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.125
IT'S GOING TO BE BAD."

00:07:29.125 --> 00:07:32.999
Alda: 
DAVE ANDERSON IS ONE  
OF THE FEW BIOLOGISTS

00:07:32.999 --> 00:07:35.999
WITH PERMISSION TO COME 
TO THE GALAPAGOS YEAR AFTER YEAR

00:07:35.999 --> 00:07:37.999
TO PURSUE HIS RESEARCH.

00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:40.999
THE RULES GOVERNING HIS VISITS 
ARE STRICT

00:07:40.999 --> 00:07:42.999
AND EVERYTHING HE BRINGS IN 
MUST GO OUT.

00:07:46.417 --> 00:07:47.999
MOCKINGBIRDS ARE 
A CONSTANT PRESENCE

00:07:47.999 --> 00:07:49.999
IN HIS CAMP ON ESPAÑOLA

00:07:49.999 --> 00:07:52.999
AND THEY SEEM EAGER TO VOLUNTEER 
FOR A SHOW-AND-TELL.

00:07:54.999 --> 00:07:55.999
Anderson: 
ON THIS ISLAND

00:07:55.999 --> 00:07:59.999
THE MOCKINGBIRD SPECIES IS 
LARGER THAN ON OTHER ISLANDS

00:07:59.999 --> 00:08:01.999
AND ON THIS ISLAND 
THE BEAK IS LONG AND CURVED.

00:08:01.999 --> 00:08:04.999
THEY USE THAT 
TO MOVE DIRT AROUND.

00:08:04.999 --> 00:08:06.999
THEY DIG MORE ON THIS ISLAND 
THAN ON OTHER ISLANDS.

00:08:06.999 --> 00:08:11.000
ALSO THE BREAST FEATHERS 
ARE WHITISH AND SPECKLED

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:15.999
AND SOME OF THE OTHER SPECIES 
ARE MUCH CLEANER IN THE BREAST.

00:08:15.999 --> 00:08:17.959
THE POINT IS THAT 
NEARBY ISLANDS HAVE

00:08:17.959 --> 00:08:18.999
VERY DIFFERENT-LOOKING BIRDS.

00:08:18.999 --> 00:08:20.999
IT'S NO PROBLEM 
FOR EVEN AN AMATEUR BIRDER

00:08:20.999 --> 00:08:24.999
TO KNOW THE DIFFERENCE 
BETWEEN SPECIES OF MOCKINGBIRDS.

00:08:24.999 --> 00:08:27.999
Alda: 
IN ADDITION TO 
THE ESPAÑOLA MOCKINGBIRDS

00:08:27.999 --> 00:08:30.125
TWO OTHER ISLANDS HAVE 
THEIR OWN DISTINCT SPECIES.

00:08:31.999 --> 00:08:33.999
THEN THERE'S A FOURTH SPECIES

00:08:33.999 --> 00:08:37.999
COMMON ACROSS MOST OF 
THE ISLANDS, INCLUDING HERE

00:08:37.999 --> 00:08:40.999
ON THE NORTHEASTERNMOST 
ISLAND, GENOVESA.

00:08:40.999 --> 00:08:42.667
THEY ALL LOOK 
A LITTLE DIFFERENT

00:08:42.667 --> 00:08:44.959
DEPENDING ON THE ISLAND 
THEY COME FROM?

00:08:44.959 --> 00:08:46.417
YEAH, SO FOR EXAMPLE, 
THOSE ESPAÑOLA BIRDS

00:08:46.417 --> 00:08:48.999
HAD A LOT OF SPECKLING 
ON THEIR BREASTS

00:08:48.999 --> 00:08:49.999
AND THIS ONE REALLY DOESN'T.

00:08:49.999 --> 00:08:51.999
THIS ONE'S GOT 
A CLEAN, WHITE BREAST.

00:08:51.999 --> 00:08:53.999
LOOKS CLEANER 
ALL THE WAY AROUND.

00:08:53.999 --> 00:08:57.999
THOSE ESPAÑOLA BIRDS LOOK 
SORT OF RATTY AND DIRTY.

00:08:57.999 --> 00:08:58.999
ARE YOU GOING 
TO LET HIM GO?

00:08:58.999 --> 00:09:00.999
YEAH... WE CAN TRY 
HYPNOTIZING HIM.

00:09:00.999 --> 00:09:03.999
OH-- CAN HE FLY 
IF HE'S HYPNOTIZED?

00:09:03.999 --> 00:09:05.999
HE'LL GO TO SLEEP.

00:09:05.999 --> 00:09:07.999
Alda: 
MOCKINGBIRDS JOINED 
THE GIANT TORTOISES

00:09:07.999 --> 00:09:10.999
ON DARWIN'S LIST OF CREATURES 
THAT FOR SOME MYSTERIOUS REASON

00:09:10.999 --> 00:09:12.999
WERE SLIGHTLY DIFFERENT 
ON DIFFERENT ISLANDS.

00:09:12.999 --> 00:09:15.999
I WILL NOW MAKE 
THIS MOCKINGBIRD 
WAKE UP.

00:09:15.999 --> 00:09:17.999
( snaps fingers )

00:09:17.999 --> 00:09:19.667
( laughs )

00:09:20.999 --> 00:09:23.834
YOU DIDN'T EVEN GIVE HIM 
A POST-HYPNOTIC SUGGESTION.

00:09:23.834 --> 00:09:24.834
THAT WAS AMAZING.

00:09:24.834 --> 00:09:25.999
DALE, DALE!

00:09:25.999 --> 00:09:27.999
Alda: 
DURING HIS FIVE WEEKS 
IN THE GALAPAGOS

00:09:27.999 --> 00:09:30.250
DARWIN VISITED ONLY FOUR 
OF THE ISLANDS...

00:09:30.250 --> 00:09:32.999
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

00:09:32.999 --> 00:09:35.999
Alda: 
YET HE MANAGED TO COLLECT 
HUNDREDS OF SPECIMENS

00:09:35.999 --> 00:09:37.999
OF BIRDS, ANIMALS AND PLANTS.

00:09:41.999 --> 00:09:43.999
THIS WAS ONE 
OF THE ISLANDS 
DARWIN LANDED AT?

00:09:43.999 --> 00:09:45.959
YEAH, THIS IS FLOREANA.

00:09:45.959 --> 00:09:48.999
THIS WAS HIS SECOND STOP, 
ACTUALLY, IN THE GALAPAGOS.

00:09:48.999 --> 00:09:51.999
Alda: 
BY NOW, DARWIN WAS BECOMING 
INCREASINGLY EXCITED

00:09:51.999 --> 00:09:54.999
BY THE NATURAL HISTORY 
OF THE ISLANDS.

00:09:54.999 --> 00:09:56.250
EVERYWHERE, HE WAS SEEING

00:09:56.250 --> 00:09:58.999
WHAT HE CALLED 
"ABORIGINAL CREATIONS"--

00:09:58.999 --> 00:10:01.999
ANIMALS AND PLANTS 
FOUND NOWHERE ELSE--

00:10:01.999 --> 00:10:05.999
WHAT BIOLOGISTS NOW CALL 
"ENDEMIC SPECIES."

00:10:05.999 --> 00:10:09.999
ON FLOREANA ALONE, 
HE IDENTIFIED 21 ENDEMIC PLANTS.

00:10:09.999 --> 00:10:12.999
SO, WHAT PLANTS 
HERE ARE ENDEMIC 
TO THIS ISLAND?

00:10:12.999 --> 00:10:14.959
WELL, HERE WE'VE 
GOT LECOCARPUS--

00:10:14.959 --> 00:10:15.999
THIS LITTLE YELLOW DAISY--

00:10:15.999 --> 00:10:20.834
AND THIS ONE HERE WITH THE HAIRY 
LEAVES, THIS IS SCALESIA VELOSA.

00:10:20.834 --> 00:10:22.959
Alda: 
AND ONCE AGAIN, DARWIN NOTICED

00:10:22.959 --> 00:10:25.834
THAT DIFFERENT ISLANDS HAD 
THEIR OWN UNIQUE VERSIONS

00:10:25.834 --> 00:10:28.999
INCLUDING A SPECIES OF SCALESIA 
THAT GROWS INTO A 30-FOOT TREE.

00:10:32.959 --> 00:10:33.999
BUT THERE WAS SOMETHING ELSE

00:10:33.999 --> 00:10:36.999
BESIDES THE UNIQUENESS 
OF THE PLANTS AND ANIMALS HERE.

00:10:38.999 --> 00:10:41.999
THEY SEEMED TO DARWIN 
TO BEAR A STRIKING RESEMBLANCE

00:10:41.999 --> 00:10:43.999
TO THOSE HE'D JUST SEEN 
IN SOUTH AMERICA.

00:10:43.999 --> 00:10:47.417
AND A TREMENDOUS IDEA 
BEGAN TO GERMINATE:

00:10:47.417 --> 00:10:48.999
PERHAPS HERE IN THE GALAPAGOS

