AND HE'S GOT A LOT MORE 
OVERHEAD THAN THIS ONE.

00:14:41.999 --> 00:14:42.999
Alda: 
CONTRARY TO LEGEND

00:14:42.999 --> 00:14:44.999
DARWIN HIMSELF DIDN'T 
PAY MUCH ATTENTION

00:14:44.999 --> 00:14:47.999
TO THE DULL LITTLE BIRDS THAT 
OFTEN HOPPED AROUND HIS FEET.

00:14:47.999 --> 00:14:50.999
HE COLLECTED SEVERAL DOZEN 
WHILE HE WAS HERE

00:14:50.999 --> 00:14:53.250
BUT HE DIDN'T EVEN 
BOTHER TO LABEL THEM

00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:55.999
OR NOTE WHICH ISLAND 
THEY CAME FROM.

00:14:56.999 --> 00:14:59.999
BUT BY A DELICIOUS TWIST OF FATE

00:14:59.999 --> 00:15:01.999
IT'S THE FINCHES ON ONE 
OF THE GALAPAGOS ISLANDS--

00:15:01.999 --> 00:15:03.999
AN ISLAND DARWIN 
DIDN'T EVEN VISIT--

00:15:03.999 --> 00:15:05.999
THAT HAVE BECOME 
THE SINGLE BEST PROOF

00:15:05.999 --> 00:15:08.999
THAT HIS THEORY OF EVOLUTION IS 
NO LONGER ONLY A THEORY

00:15:08.999 --> 00:15:10.999
BUT AN OBSERVABLE FACT.

00:15:10.999 --> 00:15:12.250
YEP, YEP.

00:15:12.250 --> 00:15:14.999
Alda: 
AS WE APPROACH THE ISLAND

00:15:14.999 --> 00:15:17.250
I CAN SEE 
WHY DARWIN NEVER LANDED HERE.

