IT KIND OF BOILS DOWN 
TO WHAT SEEDS ARE HERE

00:16:31.999 --> 00:16:34.250
AND "WHAT TOOL DO I HAVE 
TO CRACK THOSE SEEDS?"

00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:39.999
Alda: 
THE MAIN GROUND FINCH HERE 
IS ABOUT HALFWAY IN SIZE

00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:42.834
BETWEEN THE TWO SPECIES 
DAVE AND I LOOKED AT EARLIER.

00:16:44.999 --> 00:16:46.999
WHAT THE RESEARCHERS HAVE FOUND

00:16:46.999 --> 00:16:49.250
IS THAT WHEN SMALL SEEDS 
ARE PLENTIFUL

00:16:49.250 --> 00:16:50.999
USUALLY IN RAINY YEARS

00:16:50.999 --> 00:16:53.999
THE BEAKS OF THE BIRDS 
BORN THE FOLLOWING YEAR

00:16:53.999 --> 00:16:55.999
ARE ALSO, ON AVERAGE, SMALLER.

00:16:55.999 --> 00:16:59.999
WHEN THERE ARE PLENTY 
OF LARGE SEEDS, IN DRIER YEARS

00:16:59.999 --> 00:17:03.999
THE NEXT GENERATION HAS 
BEAKS THAT ARE LARGER.

00:17:03.999 --> 00:17:07.542
THIS IS EVOLUTION, 
AND ITS DRIVING FORCE

00:17:07.542 --> 00:17:11.834
DARWIN'S GREAT INSIGHT, 
IS NATURAL SELECTION.

00:17:11.834 --> 00:17:12.999
HERE'S WHAT'S HAPPENING.

00:17:12.999 --> 00:17:16.999
IN EVERY GENERATION OF FINCHES 
THERE'S A RANGE OF BEAK SIZES

00:17:16.999 --> 00:17:20.999
SOME A LITTLE SMALLER THAN THE 
AVERAGE, SOME A LITTLE LARGER.

00:17:20.999 --> 00:17:24.999
WHEN SMALL SEEDS ARE PLENTIFUL, 
WHEN THERE'S BEEN PLENTY OF RAIN

00:17:24.999 --> 00:17:28.999
THE SMALLER-BEAKED BIRDS ARE 
THE MORE-EFFICIENT EATERS

00:17:28.999 --> 00:17:30.999
SO THEY THRIVE 
AND PRODUCE MORE OFFSPRING

00:17:30.999 --> 00:17:32.999
THAN THE LARGER-BEAKED BIRDS.

00:17:32.999 --> 00:17:35.834
THE RESULT IS 
THAT IN THE NEXT GENERATION

00:17:35.834 --> 00:17:38.000
THERE ARE MORE SMALL- 
THAN LARGE-BEAKED BIRDS.

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:41.999
THE AVERAGE BEAK SIZE IS SMALLER 
THAN THE LAST GENERATION.

00:17:41.999 --> 00:17:44.999
THE POPULATION HAS EVOLVED.

00:17:44.999 --> 00:17:46.000
WHEN CONDITIONS CHANGE

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:49.125
AND A DRY YEAR BRINGS 
MORE LARGE SEEDS THAN SMALL

00:17:49.125 --> 00:17:51.542
THEN LARGE-BEAKED BIRDS 
DO BETTER.

00:17:51.542 --> 00:17:52.999
THEY LEAVE MORE OFFSPRING

00:17:52.999 --> 00:17:56.999
AND THE POPULATION SHIFTS TOWARD 
A LARGER AVERAGE BEAK SIZE.

00:17:56.999 --> 00:17:58.999
SMALLER TO LARGER, 
LARGER TO SMALLER--

00:17:58.999 --> 00:18:01.959
IT'S THESE SUBTLE SHIFTS 
IN BEAK SIZE

00:18:01.959 --> 00:18:04.999
THAT THE RESEARCHERS HAVE 
SO METICULOUSLY DOCUMENTED.

00:18:04.999 --> 00:18:06.999
Anderson: 
THE REALLY SIGNIFICANT THING 
THEY FOUND IS

00:18:06.999 --> 00:18:08.999
THAT OSCILLATING BACK AND FORTH

00:18:08.999 --> 00:18:11.999
THAT THE SIZE OF THE BEAK 
REALLY DOES CHANGE

00:18:11.999 --> 00:18:14.999
OVER SHORT PERIODS OF TIME, 
AND THEY KNOW EXACTLY WHY.

00:18:14.999 --> 00:18:18.959
IT'S BECAUSE THEIR 
FOOD SUPPLY CHANGES.

